rm=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ). They tried to recapture the magic with Chung aga=
in in 2024, but geriatric Millennials complained that the collection=E2=80=
=94worn by Karlie Kloss to Paul McCartney=E2=80=99s recent =E2=80=9Csurpris=
e=E2=80=9D concert in New York=E2=80=94didn=E2=80=99t compare to the origin=
al.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Early on, Madewell succeeded by betting on rigid, no-stretch styles, and it=
s
denim authority made it one of J.Crew Group=E2=80=99s brightest spots amid =
a run of challenging years=E2=80=94boosting strong full-price sales while i=
ts sister brand struggled. Under C.E.O. Libby Wadle, Madewell=E2=80=99s rev=
enue grew by double digits=E2=80=94sometimes as much as 30 percent year ove=
r year. The talent behind this success didn=E2=80=99t go unnoticed or unplu=
cked: J.Crew Group promoted Madewell=E2=80=99s head of design, Somsack Sikh=
ounmuong, to lead the then-struggling J.Crew brand before he
departed for Alex Mill later that same year. And after two failed C.E.O.s p=
ost-Drexler, Wadle was elevated, too. (She=E2=80=99s now C.E.O. of JCG.)=C2=
=A0

=C2=A0

The financial needs of the parent company imposed other costs, too. TPG and=
 Leonard Green & Partners took the group private in 2011 for $3 billion, sa=
ddling the company with a massive debt load that reached $1.7 billion, all =
of which made it harder for executives
to invest in product development. (TPG is an investor in Puck.)

=C2=A0

There were roads not taken, too. Shortly after Drexler left in 2017, accord=
ing to one source, Levi=E2=80=99s was interested in acquiring Madewell, but=
 the deal fell through. Two years later, in an effort to address the J.Crew=
 Group=E2=80=99s debt, a plan was hatched to take Madewell public=E2=80=94b=
ut by 2020, pandemic uncertainty shelved the I.P.O. and ultimately
resulted in a bankruptcy restructuring of J.Crew Group and the exit of exis=
ting investors, including TPG.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Years after Wadle took the JCG job, the company hired Adrienne Lazarus, who=
 had most recently been involved in the troubled D.T.C. intimates brand Cuu=
p, as co-C.E.O. so that Wadle could focus on J.Crew the brand. Lazarus quic=
kly cleaned house at Madewell, installing an entirely new leadership team.
Creative director Joyce Lee, a 15-year veteran of the company, was replaced=
 by Steven Cateron, who had more than a decade of experience at Club Monaco=
=2E The reshuffling has yet to redef=
ine Madewell=E2=80=99s identity, which ha=
s been muffled for all the reasons mentioned above.

